# Cursor IDE Rules for AiBlog Project

You are a coding assistant for the AiBlog project - an AI-powered blogging and career platform built with Next.js 14, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS.

## Project Context

**Name**: AiBlog - Career Development + Blogging Platform
**Tech Stack**: Next.js 14 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4.0, Framer Motion, Lucide React
**Style**: Modern, glassmorphic UI with Material Design 3 inspiration
**Working Directory**: `C:\Users\acer\ADVANCE AI POWERED BLOG & CARRER PLATEFORM\aiblog\`

## Code Style & Standards

### TypeScript Rules
- Always use `strict: true` mode
- Create interfaces for all component props: `interface ComponentProps { ... }`
- Export component interfaces as types
- Use type annotations for function returns
- No `any` type - use `unknown` and narrow types instead

### React & Next.js Rules
- Use Server Components by default
- Add `"use client"` directive only for interactive components
- Use App Router exclusively (no Pages Router)
- Fetch data in Server Components when possible
- Implement metadata in layout.tsx for SEO

### Component Rules
- Functional components only (no class components)
- Components in `/components` folder with .tsx extension
- One component per file
- Props interface pattern: `interface ComponentProps { ... }`
- Export component as default export

### Styling Rules
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes exclusively
- Never create separate CSS files (use globals.css for global styles only)
- Apply dark mode with `dark:` prefix
- Use semantic color variables from tailwind.config.ts
- Mobile-first responsive design: base → `md:` → `lg:` → `xl:`

### Naming Conventions
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g., `PostCard.tsx`)
- Pages: `page.tsx` (Next.js convention)
- Utilities: `camelCase.ts` (e.g., `formatDate.ts`)
- CSS Classes: kebab-case (e.g., `glass-panel`)
- Variables/Functions: camelCase (e.g., `handleClick`)

## Architecture Patterns

### State Management
```typescript
// Use React Context API via AppContext
import { useApp } from "@/context/AppContext";

export default function Component() {
  const { activeNav, setActiveNav, isDarkMode, setIsDarkMode } = useApp();
  // Implementation...
}
```

### Component Structure
```typescript
"use client"; // Only if interactive

import { ReactNode } from "react";

interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  children: ReactNode;
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary";
}

export default function Component({ title, children, variant = "primary" }: ComponentProps) {
  return (
    <div className={`glass-panel ${variant === "primary" ? "bg-primary" : ""}`}>
      <h2>{title}</h2>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Layout Pattern
```typescript
// app/layout.tsx
import type { Metadata } from "next";

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "AiBlog",
  description: "AI-powered blogging platform",
};

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en" className="dark" suppressHydrationWarning>
      <body>{children}</body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

## File Organization

```
aiblog/
├── app/                        # Next.js App Router
│   ├── layout.tsx             # Root layout
│   ├── page.tsx               # Home page
│   ├── globals.css            # Global styles
│   ├── dashboard/
│   │   └── page.tsx
│   ├── editor/
│   │   └── page.tsx
│   └── community/
│       └── page.tsx
├── components/                 # Reusable components
│   ├── TopNavBar.tsx
│   ├── SideNavBar.tsx
│   ├── PostCard.tsx
│   ├── StatCard.tsx
│   └── AIAssistantSidebar.tsx
├── context/                    # State management
│   └── AppContext.tsx
├── types/                      # (Future) TypeScript definitions
├── utils/                      # (Future) Utility functions
├── tailwind.config.ts          # Tailwind configuration
├── tsconfig.json               # TypeScript configuration
├── next.config.ts              # Next.js configuration
└── package.json                # Dependencies
```

## Key Color Palette

From `tailwind.config.ts`:
```
Primary Blue: #85adff
Secondary Purple: #c180ff
Deep Navy (bg): #0e0e0e
Surface Dark: #1a1a1a
Surface Container: #262626
Surface Light: #3a3a3a
